<TITLE> 40 shanties gutted in Badda fire </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 21 (bdnews24.com) About 40 shanties were gutted in a fire that swept through a slum in Badda late Thursday night, said an official with the Fire Service and Civil Defence. No casualty was reported. Badda police chief Syed Mominul Ahsan told bdnews24.com that the fire had started in a market close to the slum. The fire also burnt bamboo poles stacked up in the market. Seven units of fire fighters swung into action to dowse the fire. Golam Sarwar, a team leader of the Fire Service and Civil Defence, said the fire was brought under control at 10:25pm. The road through the area was blocked when the operation was going on. Dr Rashiduddin Ahmad, who was passing through the area, told bdnews24.com by phone that he had seen leaping flames lit up the skies. bd
